    # [Scene: Saltgarden Research Lab | Night]
    hide etta_muir
    hide maya_kestrel

    scene bg ch15_3be532_4 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: String quartet with a descending motif; a steady, inevitable beat]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The lab's lights hum; the soft rustle of pages; a distant ship's horn]
    "The town rallies in small ways. Protests form at the Skyhub pavilion; the market holds a meeting under a tarpaulin; Rafi publishes a searing feature that burns through public goodwill and forces a corporate spokesperson to"
    "issue a non-apology. They call it 'a misunderstanding.' The investors release a statement about 'community partnerships.' The brochures get a new line about 'respecting local governance.'"
    "The language changes; the harm does not."
    show ilias_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    ilias_navarro "They wanted me in the global office,' he says, not asking and not apologizing. 'I can be a voice there."
    show maya_kestrel at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_kestrel "And here?' you ask. 'Who will hold the line while you're away? The apprentices — the people who will have to live with whatever deal they sign?"

    ilias_navarro "I'll bring back what I can. I promise.' (He reaches for your hand without thinking.) 'This isn't me leaving you for good. It's…it's trying where we can no longer force a courtroom's timelines to match the ocean's."
    "Promises are small vessels. They float, they sink, they carry and leak at once. You run your thumb over your coral pendant until the carved grooves feel like a map you know by touch."

    maya_kestrel "Promise me one thing,' you say. 'If they start taking what's ours — our names, our formats, our labor — you do not become the stamp they use to sell it."

    ilias_navarro "I won't. If they try that with me, I will walk. I'll use every channel I've got to push back."

    "He looks at you like both apology and shield. You want to believe his pledge; you cling to it because there's nothing else to cling to. The town keeps humming with action, with anger, with small victories and bigger losses. Etta's dock is sold. Photographs of the sold dock appear in classifieds with a bland phrase" "Opportunities for strategic partnerships."
    "You speak at town meetings. You file demands. You draft counter-licensing terms with Dr. Hana's counsel. You show the apprentices how to navigate forms and how to record oral histories that lawyers can't patent. Your work is a thicket of small resistances."
    "But the franchise model seeps into neighboring harbors the same way mold finds a damp shelf: slow, invasive, and accepted because it offers a veneer of stability. Investors add clauses that count hours out of communities"
    "as 'service credits.' The apprenticeship model becomes a payroll line item in spreadsheets you can't reach. Some neighbors take the money. Others leave. The town's skyline — its patched roofs and handmade boats — becomes an"
    "image in glossy brochures used to sell the very replication that hollowed it out."
    hide ilias_navarro
    hide maya_kestrel

    scene bg ch15_3be532_5 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Strings resolve downward into a single, sustained note]
    "On the night before Ilias's departure, you walk the High Tide Boardwalk. The seawall gleams like a false promise. A brochure flaps in the wind, momentarily catching the edge of the railing before the tide drags"
    "it away. You press the coral pendant with raw fingers. Memory crowds you: the day you closed your notebook and felt 'Begin' as a literal thing; the apprentices' first stitches; Etta's hands on the dock."
    "There is proof that you did something that mattered. There is proof that your model saved lives in the immediate months it was deployed. That truth hums like a lamp behind the more painful fact: what"
    "you made available was taken and reshaped into rents and quotas that make livelihood into line items."
    show ilias_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    ilias_navarro "Write what you must. Fight with everything you have here.' (He pauses, then forces a half-smile.) 'And call me if you find a way to make them listen."
    "When the plane disappears, the town doesn't stop existing. It reshapes. People adapt. Some find dignity in new forms; others do not. Etta writes from a small coastal town inland, her letters sharp and relaxed by"
    "turns. Rafi's pieces win awards and then find themselves ghosted in the eyes of those whose livelihoods were bought. Seren Blake's firm reports 'successful scaling' to shareholders; an internal memo — leaked by someone who still"
    "sleeps badly at night — uses Hearthbend as a showcase."
    "You keep your notebook closed sometimes, because seeing the memos is a wound you have to open again. Other times you open it and add names of those who left, dates stamped like small tombstones. You"
    "catalog what you can: contracts, photographer credits, apprentice testimonies. You teach a workshop on legal literacy and show a room full of neighbors how to find a clause and mark it."
    "And still the pendant feels heavy."
    hide ilias_navarro

    scene bg ch15_3be532_6 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A single cello line that settles, then fades]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The tide pulling back; distant, unrelenting]
    "There is no neat closure. The rise that came fast left a different kind of erosion — one born of your own choices and the seductive optimism that a model could be both open and resilient"
    "under the pressures of capital. You feel culpable in ways that a storm's randomness would never ask of you: culpable because you signed, because you believed, because you trusted systems to be better than they were."
    "You map the losses: Etta's dock sold; apprentices bound by rent-like clauses; the market with fewer fisherfolk and more managers; Ilias gone to a world that needs him but will not feel exactly the same as"
    "Hearthbend. Yet irrigation of small, stubborn life continues — neighbors garden on rooftops, someone reinstalls a hand-painted sign, a child learns to tie a knot the old way because you taught it in a legal-literacy class."
    "You are tired. You are furious. You are grieving. But you do not stop."
    show maya_kestrel at left:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_kestrel "We did this so others wouldn't have to start from nothing.' (Your voice cracks, then steadies.) 'We were right to try. We were wrong to trust them with everything."
    "The pendant rests at your throat, heavier than when the chapter began but still a thing you can carry. You fold your notebook closed and tuck it under your arm like an artifact that must be"
    "preserved, not because it will heal everything, but because the record matters. You will keep teaching, keep drafting counter-licenses, keep naming the harm when it comes. That is how you honor what you have and what"
    "you lost."
    "You walk back into Hearthbend, into the damp light, carrying both the proof of your work and the stain of its extraction. The town's contours remain — altered, sometimes hollowed, sometimes stubbornly alive. You light a"
    "small candle at the harbor memorial and watch the flame shiver in the salt wind; you think of a ledger you once tried to balance on your own and realize the balance is never perfect. It"
    "will never be perfect. But people are still here."
    hide maya_kestrel

    scene bg ch15_3be532_7 at full_bg
